reviewText: This is another light comedy with slapstick in the continuing series of 1940's Hal Roach streamliner movies with William Tracy and Joe Sawyer.  This one also features Noah Beery, Jr. as a fellow army sergeant.  The good guy wins and the bad guys get their just desserts.
Sergeant Doubleday being tossed out the window was hilarious!
I am just finding Willam Tracy movies. He was a good actor.
Love movie wish had more of him  of William tracy
I saw this movie at my Dad's house it is really funny if you get a chance check this movie out.
